author: COMSOL
description: In this tutorial example, the concepts of Component Mode Synthesis (CMS) are introduced through a simple solid model of a beam. Parts of the beam are reduced into CMS components. Dynamic as well as stationary analyses are performed. Moreover, you will learn how to apply loads directly on a CMS component and how to work with such components during result evaluation. The results from the full and the reduced versions of the model are compared.
label: cms_tutorial.mph
